<FIRST>r a AM-BRF--TexasBusCrash     10-08 0119</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-BRF--Texas Bus Crash,0122</SECOND>
<HEAD>Truck Collides With School Bus, 1 Injured</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ROSENBERG, Texas (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A pickup truck collided head-on with a
school bus carrying students from a county fair Saturday,
critically injuring the truck driver. Twenty students and a teacher
were sent to a hospital for observation.
   The students and teacher were treated and released from a local
hospital. The 29-year-old truck driver was flown by helicopter to
an emergency room.
   The students had participated in the livestock competition at
the Fort Bend County Fair near Rosenberg, 10 miles southwest of
Houston.
   The southbound truck drove into the northbound lane, striking
the bus, as the two vehicles rounded a curve, Rosenberg Police Sgt.
Beverly Johnson said.
</TEXT>
