<HEAD>Men Wearing Masks of Former Presidents Botch Robbery</HEAD>
<DATELINE>OMAHA, Neb. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Two armed men wearing masks resembling former
Presidents Reagan and Carter attempted to rob a bank but a
fast-acting employee locked them out. One man was shot in the arm.
   The men apparently staked out the Mid-City Bank and waited for
employees to arrive Saturday, Police Sgt. Richard Dragoun said.
   When one woman arrived about 7 a.m., the men grabbed her and
held her in a lobby between inner and outer doors, Dragoun said.
When they tried to push their way into the main lobby, the woman
escaped and locked the inner lobby door behind her, he said.
   One of the men fired a shot through the doors, striking bank
president James Fitl in the right arm. Relatives said he was in
good condition at Clarkson Hospital.
   No arrests had been made by Sunday, police said.
